<threat_model>
## Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| in-process injected DLL â†’ exe export | An already-injected DLL (Utinni) calls GetProcAddress + 
GetEngineHookPoints. No external/network/untrusted input crosses any boundary; the export takes zero 
arguments. |

## STRIDE Threat Register

| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| T-37-01 | Information Disclosure | GetEngineHookPoints exposing internal fn/global addresses | 
accept | The addresses are already fully discoverable by any code running in-process (an injected 
DLL has the entire address space + can read the PE/PDB). The export adds no privilege beyond what 
injection already grants. This is the cooperative contract by design (spec Â§0). |
| T-37-02 | Tampering | A wrong `&` advertising the wrong function (worse than a missing row, spec 
Â§0) | mitigate | Spike rows are copied verbatim from source-confirmed symbols; the EPA-02 
crash-fixer uses the RESEARCH-corrected thunk (installConfigFileOverride, NOT loadFromBuffer). The 
/FORCE link-grep (0 unresolved) + dumpbin gate catch missing/typo'd symbols. Runtime no-null/no-dup 
self-check seeds the coverage gate. |
| T-37-03 | Denial of Service | Stale-plugin ABI cascade from a shared-header touch (AGENTS.md) | 
mitigate | utinni_engine_hookpoints.h is NEW and consumed ONLY by the exe (utinni_advertise.cpp). It 
is NOT added to any shared header the plugins compile (acceptance check: no engine includes in the 
.h; not referenced by any gl0X vcxproj). Risk: none if kept exe-local. |
</threat_model>

